            All his career, <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Bob Dole</ENAMEX>
has stood for fiscal conservatism and balanced budgets. Most famously, he was
almost alone among <ENAMEX TYPE="NATIONALITY">Republican</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">leaders</ENAMEX> in his caustic skepticism about the
supply-side economics of <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">the 1980s</TIMEX>. Now, political and economic <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">advisers</ENAMEX> are
urging the <ENAMEX TYPE="NATIONALITY">Republican</ENAMEX> presidential <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">candidate</ENAMEX> to take off his green eyeshade,
push aside that unappetizing bowl of budget cuts, and scarf down a tasty dose
of tax-cut rejuvenator. Just the tonic for <ENAMEX TYPE="DISEASE">anemic</ENAMEX> poll numbers. And <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Dole</ENAMEX> is
