response to lower taxes. The <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">group</ENAMEX> whose work effort increased most
sharply was not the well-paid, whose tax rates declined most sharply. It was
the poorly paid, whose marginal tax rates, thanks to <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Social Security</ENAMEX> tax hikes,
